<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with a top-3 case candidates list + a preliminary stakeholder-perspective leaning. The path you pick is about how you want to consider the options.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have chosen my case and my stakeholder, I can articulate why my stakeholder's perspective is worth representing, and I have identified what about my stakeholder I might find hardest to defend.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Walk all 8 case cards + jot top-3 (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Read all 8 case cards in the <a href="/units/unit-5/assessment-water-stakeholders/">assessment handout</a>. For each, write one sentence on why it's interesting to YOU specifically. Then pick a top 3 + sketch a preliminary stakeholder perspective for your #1.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Source-test your top choice (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you already have a strong sense of your top case, source-test it: in 25 minutes, find one government source, one news source, and one NGO source about a contested claim in that case. Quick-OPVL each. If the source set is thin or all sides agree (unlikely on a real water dispute), reconsider.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-discuss with overlapping interest (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Find a partner with overlapping interest in 1-2 cases. Discuss what each of you would do differently with the same case + different stakeholders. Useful for clarifying YOUR angle without duplicating someone else's.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Stretch-vs-default decision support (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">The hard pedagogical pick: do you take a stakeholder perspective that <em>isn't</em> your own default (stretch — stronger T/T outcome), or stick with your default sympathy (safer)? Come to the peer-help table for a 5-minute think-aloud. Either choice is allowed; the rubric reflects the choice.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

